Process for updating repo:

1) **Pull** to get any updates

2) **Staging** (adding the files to the queue to send to the repo)
 - In the Git menu: click on the box by individual files to stage them
 - in the terminal: (to do all files)
 git add .
 
3) **Commit** (sending the file to the repo to commit to an update)
- in the Git menu: click commit and write a brief message
- in the terminal:
 git commit -m "a brief message indicating that you're sending"
 
4) **Push** files to the repo
- in the commit pop-up: click "push"
- in the terminal:
 git push

************************************
************************************
If you get ahead on branches:
 git reset HEAD~1
(You can change the 1 to other vaules if you are ahead by more than one commit)
